      <p class="lead">No developer wants to wait on <strong>that one, outdated device</strong> to use an awesome new API. But if you’re building hybrid apps for Android, you’re normally left not choice.</p>
      <p>You’re forced to assume every Android <code>WebView</code> works differently (because it probably does). There’s variations in:
      <ul>
        <li>Which JavaScript APIs are available</li>
        <li>The syntax for CSS properties</li>
        <li>How your app’s interface renders</li>
      </ul>
      <p>…and plenty more. Of course you want to support every version of Android you can—but it’s frustrating and time consuming. And you’re <strong>still</strong> not able to that one new feature!</p>
      <p>What if the only <code>WebView</code> you had to worry about was like the latest version of Google Chromium?</p>
    </div>
